			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Teliris is the provider of the world&rsquo;s most innovative fully managed telepresence and collaboration technology, which realistically replicates the human dynamics of an in-person meeting experience, with installations in 37 countries around the world.</p>
<p>
We are currently searching for an Sr. Accountant in our NYC offices. This will be a fun and challenging job for the right candidate, with heavy interaction with our CFO and other members of the Sr Management team.</p>
<p>
This is a hands on accounting position for the right candidate and will be responsible for ensuring the integrity of accounting information in creating timely and accurate financial statements. This role will be responsible for Month end closing tasks, bank reconciliations, software capitalization, bank covenant reporting, intercompany transfers, foreign currencies, audit reporting, fixed asset and inventory accounting, among other responsibilities.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate will have:</p>
<ul>
<li>
BS Degree in Accounting</li>
<li>
Seven to ten years experience in all aspects of accounting</li>
<li>
Experience with Microsoft Office, expert level Excel skills</li>
<li>
Experience with Microsoft Dynamics preferred</li>
<li>
Knowledgeable of inventory process</li>
<li>
CPA is preferred but not required</li>
<li>
Experience with SFAS Rules</li>
</ul>
<p>
Teliris is a dynamic company and and we value honesty, articulate independent thinkers and proactive people that are eager to learn and contribute, and not content to sit around and wait for instructions.</p>
<p>
We offer strong compensation and benefits, in casual and entrepreneurial work culture.</p>
<p>
In lieu of a cover letter, please submit your resume along with 4 bullet points describing why you&rsquo;d be a good fit for the role, and include your salary requirements. Submittals without this information unfortunately cannot be considered. NYC metro local candidates only, please.</p>
<p>
We are an equal opportunity employer.</p>
<p>
Please respect our time. No phone calls, and no recruiters, please.</p>
